  "prompt": "Can i send my GRE scores to the four universities freely?",
  "response": "Yes, you can send your GRE scores to up to four universities for free, but only if you select those institutions on the test day. When you take the GRE, before you see your scores, you will have the option to designate up to four institutions to receive your scores at no additional cost. These score reports will be sent to the universities along with your official GRE scores.\n\nIf you decide to send your scores after the test day, you will need to pay a fee for each additional score report you send. As of recent information, the cost is around $27 per score report.\n\nSo, to take advantage of the free score sends, make sure you have your list of four institutions ready when you take the GRE.",
